con:testCase.con:description:
S18601 Name: Portster DB - Import Working Numbers Description: Create POST /portster/v1/admin/phoneNumbers/workingQxReport Example of the call in INTG: curl -XPOST http://corp-zzeus.lab.af.qwest.net/portster/v1/admin/phoneNumbers/workingQxReport -T workingQX.csv
Data example in workingQX.csv: TN, ORDER_NUMBER 2012963001,R23757048444305648 2012963002,R23759037544400525 2012963003,R23759820644478459 2012963004,R23776364045330466 2012963005,R23776364045330466
To verfiy successful load of data: 1) check the log and see: 5 CNUM working QX numbers are successfully recorded in the database. From total 6 lines in the file the 1st line (header) was skipped.
2) (for test in dev) ssh root@moniker-masterd1 (password Phot0n$!) sudo -u postgres psql portster select * from cnum_qx_working;
All the previous data in this table have to be replaced with the newly submitted data
